    "Together with 3.1, (i), it follows that ρ *: π 1 (B) → G.Conversely, we must show that any solution (g B, ρ, h) to (20) gives rise to an invariant expanding Ricci soliton on M satisfying Ansatz 3.1.",
    "We set M:= B × ρ N, which has a canonical flat connection H induced from that of the universal cover B → B, with monodromy ρ.",
    "The data (g B, H, h) defines an invariant metric g on M satisfying (i).We claim that also 3.1, (ii) holds.",
    "To see that, let U i × 𝔫 be a trivialisation for adM adapted to the flat connection ∇ ad.",
    "The bundle metric becomes a map h: U i → G/K."
